  "prompt": "What is the condition of alcohol ban in Bihar?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Bihar has maintained a complete ban on the sale and consumption of alcohol since April 2016. The Bihar government implemented this prohibition as part of its policy to promote social welfare and reduce alcohol-related issues. The ban includes a variety of alcoholic beverages, and violations can lead to significant penalties, including fines and imprisonment.\n\nOver the years, the enforcement of this ban has seen various challenges and has generated significant debate within the state, with some reports of illegal bottlegging and consumption still occurring. The state's government has also launched awareness programs to educate citizens about the negative effects of alcohol consumption.\n\nFor the most current and detailed information on the status of alcohol laws in Bihar, it's advisable to consult official government sources or recent news reports, as policies can evolve over time.",
